name: float_f64_one_plus_epsilon
description: |
  This is the binary64 value immediately above 1, exactly 1 + 2^-52. The pair
  differs by one unit in the last place, so it probes approximate-equality
  thresholds, lossy serialization, and displays that round both values to the
  same short decimal string.
format: hex
decode-as: f64
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "epsilon"
  - "ulp"
  - "precision"
---
01 00 00 00 00 00 f0 3f   # 0x3ff0000000000001: next value above 1
